      <title>Former Vice President Dick Cheney dies. And, Election Day races to watch</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2025/11/04/g-s1-96433/up-first-briefing-former-vp-dick-cheney-dies-election-day-races</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2025/11/04/g-s1-96433/up-first-briefing-former-vp-dick-cheney-dies-election-day-races</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2025/11/04/g-s1-96433/up-first-briefing-former-vp-dick-cheney-dies-election-day-races</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 04 Nov 2025 12:53:20 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dick Cheney, widely regarded as the most powerful vice president in American history, died yesterday&lt;/strong&gt;, according to a statement from his family. He was 84. The cause of death was complications of pneumonia and cardiac and vascular disease, the statement added. Read more about his life and legacy &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/11/04/123987715/dick-cheney-former-vice-president-dies" target="_blank"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-96428-1" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3739;         --source-height: 2493;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3739x2493+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F8f%2Fc6598a644ba7adc17c3a99829502%2Fgettyimages-1415300334.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3739x2493+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F8f%2Fc6598a644ba7adc17c3a99829502%2Fgettyimages-1415300334.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3739x2493+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd6%2F8f%2Fc6598a64